"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    Closure of the incision, with a Jackson&ndash;Pratt drain exiting the skin of the low axilla and secured externally with a nylon suture. With the drain under the lower ���������ap, it catches the ���������uid dependently.",
"    <br>",
"     (A) The incision with a simple closure of the ellipse.",
"     <br>",
"      (B) With a Y-plasty modi���������cation in the context of those larger individuals who have developed a ridge of tissue extending to the lateral thorax or back secondary to the weight of the breast over time. This closure results in reducing the excess tissue laterally, beyond the breast, which may stick out after closure. Closure of the skin-sparing incisions is not depicted, as it is generally used in the context of collaboration with a plastic surgeon who will reconstruct before closure.",
